queryParams.description: To dial an extension number, the format is: tel:+16177123000;postd=1234. However, if you do outbound dialing to an extension, you would want to use a <record> tag to account for the hold music that is played while you are being transferred to the extension and to ensure that your prompts are played at the correct time.  To specify the caller ID on a per call basis, you'll have to change your phone_number parameter to also include the caller ID you want the call recipient to see. The format is: phone_number=tel:+10123456789;ani=1234567890. This would make an outbound call to 012-345-6789 and display a caller ID of 123-456-7890.
